  "response": "The experience of being dead is something that remains unknown and is subject to speculation, philosophy, and various cultural beliefs. Since there is no scientific evidence or consensus on the experience of death itself, opinions vary widely. Some believe in an afterlife or reincarnation, while others see death as a natural end to consciousness without any experience afterward. Ultimately, it is a profound mystery that each belief system interprets in its own way.",
